title: UGA heavy favorite over Kentucky in SEC East showdown
title_page: UGA football: Dogs heavy favorites over Kentucky in SEC East showdown
text:
- Georgia not surprised Kentucky is playing for division title
The Georgia Bulldogs are 9 1/2-point favorites over Kentucky in a game that will determine the SEC East champion on Saturday, according to VegasInsider.com.
No. 6 Georgia (7-1, 5-1 SEC) faces No. 11 Kentucky (7-1, 5-1 SEC) in a nationally-televised game with a berth in the Dec. 1 SEC Championship Game on the line. (Game can be heard on WSB 750 AM and 95.5 FM). Georgia has won the last eight games in the series, including a 42-13 victory in Athens in 2017.
- Legend of Rodrigo born two years ago vs. Kentucky
Georgia has won in its last five trips to Lexington, although the last game was a hard-fought 27-24 victory in 2016. Here’s a look at the last five games in the series:
2017: Georgia 42, Kentucky 13 (Athens)
2016: Georgia 27, Kentucky 24 (Lexington)
2015: Georgia 27, Kentucky 3 (Athens)
2014: Georgia 63, Kentucky 31 (Lexington)
2013: Georgia 59, Kentucky 17 (Athens)
- Mark Bradley: For UGA, it’s a big game. For Kentucky, it’s historic
